The paper discusses the SP theory of intelligence, which is a theory that aims to simplify and integrate ideas across artificial intelligence, mainstream computing, and human perception and cognition. The theory has potential applications in several areas of computing and cognition, including unsupervised learning, natural language processing, autonomous robots, computer vision, intelligent databases, software engineering, information compression, medical diagnosis, big data, and more. These areas of application are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
